Subject: [PATCH 06/17] Add location_id to testimonies, stamped by client at
 submission
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

XXX[back]: traces client (Testimony.jsx location_id prop, resolved via
I18N('location.' + id)) needs the recording machine's physical location
attached to each new testimony. This is not visitor input â€” the client
is meant to stamp it from its own local config at submission time.

Adds a nullable location_id TEXT column to testimonies (existing rows
get NULL), threads it through Testimony/RawTestimony, and accepts it
as an optional `l` query param on POST /testimony. The traces client
does not send this param yet (API.js#pushTestimony has no such key),
so submissions will keep getting location_id: null until that lands.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
